Members of Congress, as well as cabinet members and state officials, responded positively to President Trump's State of the Union address. They praised his vision for America, his commitment to bipartisanship, and his achievements in areas such as the economy, job growth, and national security. They also expressed support for his proposals on issues such as border security, infrastructure, healthcare, and criminal justice reform. Advocacy and policy organizations, including The AIDS Institute, American Trucking Associations, Concerned Women for America, and The Heritage Foundation, also commended the President's speech and his policy agenda.